						               													<description>Goita is a traditional game played since the early 20th century  in Ushitsu, a district of Noto town, Ishikawa region in Japan.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sankaku Goita Clear' is a&amp;#227;&amp;#128;&amp;#128;development of the classic game Goita,which can be played with &amp;quot;Sankaku Goita&amp;quot;.(This is normal Goita, made of triangle wooden piece, packed in the small case, of which bottom board is usable as a scoreboard.)&amp;#10;The clear pieces make you see through half of the pieces at hand so that you can enjoy different strategies from the normal one!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;[How to play] &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Prepare the half of Sankaku Goita (16 normal pieces) and Sankaku Goita Clear (16 clear pieces).&amp;#10;     Divide those 32 pieces to the players in either way below; &amp;#10;         Half &amp;amp; Half: Put all the clear pieces in the bag and pick them up in order so that all the players have 4 clear pieces each. Then put normal pieces in a circle face down and pick them up in order again.  &amp;#10;         Random Deal: Put all the pieces of normal and clear in a circle and pick them up in order. (In this case, the number of clear and normal pieces at hand are at random.)&amp;#10;    &amp;#10;     Play as normal Goita with those divided pieces. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
